<!-- SC_OFF --><div class="md"><p>For a while now the <code>linux-headers</code> package on my pc seems broken. During update/reinstallation of the package, pacman complains about two missing files: <code> warning: could not get file information for usr/lib/modules/6.2.13-arch1-1/build/include/generated/autoconf.h warning: could not get file information for usr/lib/modules/6.2.13-arch1-1/build/include/generated/rustc_cfg </code></p> <p>and dkms isn&#39;t able to compile any kernel modules, since they all need the <code>generated/autoconf.h</code>. (Fortunately none of those modules are required for my computer to boot.)</p> <p>Running <code>sudo pacman -Qkk linux-headers</code> gives <code> warning: linux-headers: /usr/lib/modules/6.2.13-arch1-1/build/include/generated/autoconf.h (No such file or directory) warning: linux-headers: /usr/lib/modules/6.2.13-arch1-1/build/include/generated/rustc_cfg (No such file or directory) warning: linux-headers: /usr/lib/modules/6.2.13-arch1-1/build/scripts/kconfig/.conf.cmd (Modification time mismatch) warning: linux-headers: /usr/lib/modules/6.2.13-arch1-1/build/scripts/kconfig/conf (Modification time mismatch) warning: linux-headers: /usr/lib/modules/6.2.13-arch1-1/build/scripts/kconfig/conf (Size mismatch) warning: linux-headers: /usr/lib/modules/6.2.13-arch1-1/build/scripts/kconfig/conf (MD5 checksum mismatch) warning: linux-headers: /usr/lib/modules/6.2.13-arch1-1/build/scripts/kconfig/conf (SHA256 checksum mismatch) linux-headers: 19272 total files, 4 altered files </code> which implies, that even more is wrong with this packages.</p> <p>Clearing the pacman cache and reinstalling the headers doesn&#39;t change anything.</p> <p>How can the simple process of installing a package misbehave like this?</p> </div><!-- SC_ON --> &#32; submitted by &#32; <a href="https://www.reddit.com/user/OlgOron"> /u/OlgOron </a> <br/> <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/archlinux/comments/132pvdi/missing_files_in_linuxheaders_package/">[link]</a></span> &#32; <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/archlinux/comments/132pvdi/missing_files_in_linuxheaders_package/">[comments]</a></span>